        <h3 class="mini-headers">Tips</h3>
        <ol>
          <li class="tip">Dress Code - When you go to an interview make sure you’re dressed really smartly, first impressions go a long way you want to make sure the interviewer remembers you for all the right reasons.</li>
          <li class="tip">Preparation - Go to websites which will give you an insight into the company like Glassdoor and gain perspective as to what it’s like to work there. Go to the company’s website and find out how they actually mark your video or face to face interviews.</li>
          <li class="tip"> Be Confident - From the moment you walk into the room your assessment has begun. You don’t need to be the loudest person in the room but you need to carry yourself confidently and have faith that the job is yours.</li>
        </ol>
